<TITLE> UK airspace to stay closed until Tuesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, Apr 19 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - British airspace will remain closed to flights until 1 a.m. on Tuesday at the earliest because of the danger posed by clouds of volcanic ash from Iceland, aviation officials said. The air traffic body NATS said although the official weather forecaster the Met Office had advised the volcano was less active than before, restrictions would remain. "Conditions around the movement of the layers of the volcanic ash cloud over the UK remain dynamic," NATS said in a statement. "We will continue to monitor the location of this ash cloud and look for opportunities to get aircraft moving again, whilst of course maintaining safety." It said it would continue to review the situation with the Met Office, the government and airlines and would issue an update around 3 p.m. Mon
